<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It's all fine and dandy that you like Robert E. Lee and the Rebel Flag. Super, Yippy Skippy. That's not the point. The point is what it represents to a rather large population of Americans.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
This is the GA flag, not the USA flag. It's not a matter of what the flag represents to the rest of the US, as much as what it represents to Georgians.<br>
<br>
I grew up in Macon - spent close to 30 years there - and I can tell you that the confederate flag does not represent racism to me. It represents local pride and local traditions despite defeat, it represents lessons learned and a helluva lot of history.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>It seems almost painful for some of you to see what it actually represented at the time. Ya know, the &quot;real&quot; reason for that little Civil War thingy that happened.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
Please enlighten us about the &quot;real&quot; reason the civil war was fought.<br>
<br>
<br>
What cheeses me off the most about this debate is the &quot;carpetbaggers&quot;. After the civil war, carpetbaggers moved to the south loudly explaining they were there to help &quot;rebuild&quot;. In reality, they came to exploit. They especially came to exploit the newly-freed blacks, for they saw cheap labor and lots of cash. Carpetbaggers decimated an already hemorrhaging economy, and only made worse already strained racial tensions. 100 years after the war, most southern states had still not recovered from the economic damage and racial tensions were at an all-time high.<br>
<br>
In the 1970s, Georgia made significant strides towards rebuilding the economy and resolving the racial problems. The Georgia of today is is a thriving, productive member of the US, and while there may still be racial problems, they are no worse (and in many respects significantly less) than racial problems found elsewhere in the US.<br>
<br>
Now the carpetbaggers are back. They're relatively recent immigrants who have gotten all offended by the confederate flag, and now they'll help &quot;improve&quot; GA's image by redoing the flag. Thanks, guys! <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://pub75.ezboard.com/btheshoemakers"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.pwshift.com/tr/images/sigs/6Fims.jpg" style="border:0;"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
