<br>
I liked this quote, because it helped me look back on my childhood and early teen years, then my progression into adulthood.<br>
<br>
My first home was given to my mother and my father from my grandmother. My second home was a trailer for 3 years. My third home was a town home for 4 years. My fourth home was a small 3 bedroom, 2 bath house in the hood for 6 years. My fifth home was a large 3 bedroom, 2 bath house in an upper middle class area for 10 years.<br>
<br>
To come to a point, I have lived on all levels of economy. I don't remember much of my early childhood, but the things I do remember were ALWAYS fights about money. ALWAYS. When my family moved to Memphis, our first home was in the hood. We lived there for 6 years. Same problems. When we lived in the hood, and as I made friends with people of other races, I learned an early lesson, and one I stick by today.<br>
<br>
I don't feel that the racial problems today are spawned by the beliefs of some people. I believe they are answers to an economic problem. Find something easy to rest your thoughts on. Why blame yourself for your problem. Look around, find a trend.<br>
<br>
I have seen and felt racial hate in its purest form. You ever hear of the salt and pepper fight after school? Yeah, that was my poor white self getting beat down by a bunch of poor black kids. And you know what? I don't think it was racial so much as it was economic.<br>
<br>
White people brought Africans here for slavery, for oppression. So it's easy to think that white people are still trying to do it. Some are (KKK, NeoNazis, etc.). Most aren't (free thinking, productive, freedom speakers).<br>
<br>
The Confederate Flag was flown when we had African slaves. The Confederate Flag, in terms of history, has no bearing on anyone of any other race creed or religion, than those white living in America, the blacks living in America, and the slaves from the Caribbean, who were also mostly African anyway.<br>
<br>
If you want to say the Confederate Flag stands for racism, I'll start waving a 13 colonies flag and it would stand for the same damn thing, it just doesn't specifically name the south like I would want something to do. The confederate flag is the milestone for the Emancipation Proclamation, it is the last one that stood during times of slavery, and the one that was brought down after abolishment. <br>
<br>
It never stood for slavery, it stood for confederacy. Ulysses Grant didn't fight to free slaves. Ulysses Grant fought to save the Union. He had slaves even after the war that he had to free. Ulysses Grant and Abraham Lincoln aren't the bastions of racial freedom, they only worked to further lessen the morale of the Southern idiots who broke away from the Union.<br>
<br>
So no, when I fly the confederate flag, it's a history lesson, and it shows where I come from. If to you that means I'm a racist, then I have nothing to discuss with you. That makes you simple minded, a racist in your own regard, and a being I have no time for. <p><!--EZCODE HR START--><hr /><!--EZCODE HR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.ancientsaga.com/index.php" target="top">Ancient Saga</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Maxximuus Ludicruus - 60 Wizard<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE MAIL START--><a href="mailto:Maxximuus@earthlink.net"> Maxximuus@earthlink.net</a><!--EZCODE MAIL END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#102960><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sunmina>Sunmina</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Lonely in Kera Ridge</span><br>  Posts: 151<br> <font color=#628CBC>(4/9/03 3:44:44 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=520.topic&index=47>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Georgia Flag</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Exactly! *Most* of the people I speak to that think the Confederate Flag is a symbol of racism ALSO think the civil war was fought over slavery.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
