<br>
When the Confederate flag is displayed, think about the purpose of it.  Sometimes it is displayed as a symbol of racism, but a significant portion of the time it is not.  I have never seen a swastika displayed *not* as a symbol of racism.  Compare it to a cross.  It is not a symbol of hate, until you light it on fire.  It is the presentation and intent that makes it a symbol of hate.<br>
<br>
The Confederate flag has redeeming values.  Name some of those that the Swastika has.  I can't think of any.<br>
<br>
People that don't display the confederate flag hatefully have a valid argument here.  I don't care if you are offended by it, if you can't figure out the intention. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <br><font color=#628CBC>- </font><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/bmtboards>Morell-Thule Forums</a><font color=#628CBC> - </font><a href=http://pub169.ezboard.com/fmtboardsfrm5>Off Topic</a> <font color=#628CBC> - </font><a href="http://sevendragons.net">Morell-Thule Community Website</a><font color=#628CBC> - </font> <center><form name=f>Select Message Board:<br>
